PN,30408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1777179877
OL,3,CStarmer says there was only 'everyday
OL,4,Cpressure' to clear Mandelson
OL,5,Cappointment
OL,7,FYouGov projections this week indicated
OL,8,FLabour was on course for disastrous
OL,9,Fresults in its former London and Welsh
OL,10,Fstrongholds.
OL,12,FHe told The Sunday Times he would
OL,13,Ffight the next general election and
OL,14,Fthat he thinks Labour can win.
OL,16,FMeanwhile, polling of Labour members
OL,17,Fshowed that the overwhelmingly
OL,18,Fmajority think Sir Keir has handled
OL,19,Fthe Mandelson affair badly.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1777179877
OL,3,CStarmer says there was only 'everyday
OL,4,Cpressure' to clear Mandelson
OL,5,Cappointment
OL,7,FHowever, around two-thirds (61%) think
OL,8,Fhe should not resign over the scandal,
OL,9,Fwhile 29% said he should, the
OL,10,FSurvation poll for Labour List showed.
OL,12,FThey were split on whether Labour
OL,13,Fshould change its leadership, with 46%
OL,14,Fin favour and 44% saying Sir Keir
OL,15,Fshould remain in post.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/9
